    <baseline year="2014">
     <comment>
      <narrative xml:lang="PT">There is no ODS Waste Management System in Brazil.</narrative>
     </comment>
    </baseline>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2020-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2020-12-31"></period-end>
     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="PT">Assessment of the necessary adaptations in ODSs Destruction Plant and improvements in regeneration centers</narrative>
      </comment>
     </target>
     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="PT">After the Burning Test has been concluded, Essencis incinerator obtained the CETESB Operation License for burning ODS (gaseous and liquid) and has already started the incineration. Essencis incinerator has already received 3,386kg of ODS from Ecosuporte, (around 31% of the total temporarily stored in this Reclaim Center) and entire amount has already been incinerated. Ecosuporte had an unforeseen event because of the Covid-19 pandemic, as some employees who contracted the virus, stayed away for the treatment of the disease, which resulted in a delay in the transfer and the sending of more waste to the incinerator, according to the schedule incineration. According to a company representative, the operation is almost normal and the transfer operation has restarted.

As a contingency measure, It was anticipated the sending of Frigelars ODSs, located in S&#xE3;o Paulo also (near the Essencis incinerator), 979kg, which corresponds 100% of all temporarily stored quantity in this Reclaim Center. Furthermore, the necessary measures are being adopted to transport 100% of the substances stored in the CRN (ready for transport). This RC is located in Recife / Pernambuco. CRN has the longest distance from the incinerator (approximately 2,700km). This transport is expected to take place by the end of October 2020.

The installation of the Gas Chromatography System at CRN was also delayed by the advent of the pandemic. Measures are already being taken to redefine the schedule, however, it is not possible to set a deadline for completion of this activity yet.

Memorandum of Understanding, MoUs, were signed with the 4 RCs and currently UNDP monitors what is agreed in the documents. The monitoring foresee the issuance of quarterly reports prepared by RCs containing information on: purity analysis tests carried out during the period, documents and licenses related to the laboratories activities, such as: registration with the Regional Chemistry Council, licenses from the Federal Police and the Ministry of the Army (if applicable), environmental authorization for expired / obsolete reagents (chemical reagents), PPE sheets for laboratory employees and Risk and Safety Certificate.

Essencis MoU is still under evaluation by the parties.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </actual>
    </period>
